SIMPLE: intercessor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intercessor
<hw>In`ter*ces"sor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a surety:
cf. F. <ets>intercesseur</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who goes between, or intercedes; a
mediator.</def> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One who interposes between parties at
variance, with a view to reconcile them.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One who
pleads in behalf of another.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A bishop, who, during a vacancy
of the see, administers the bishopric till a successor is
installed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intercessorial</ent>⟦br⟧
